XQuartz license information
============================

XQuartz is not released under a single license. It is a distribution of
many independent components — the X.Org X server and libraries, the
`quartz-wm` window manager, Mesa, fontconfig, FreeType, Cairo, Sparkle, and
dozens more, each a separate git submodule under `src/` — and each carries
whatever license its own upstream project uses. It is not practical to
reproduce all of them here precisely; this file gives an overview and
points to where the authoritative text lives.

For the full picture, see:

- The X.Org Foundation's license summary: https://www.x.org/releases/current/doc/xorg-docs/Licenses.html
- `pkg/resources/LICENSE.txt` in this repository, installed alongside the
  built `.pkg` and shown to end users during installation.
- The individual license/copyright header in each source file, and each
  submodule's own `COPYING`/`LICENSE` file where present.

As a representative example, the core XQuartz application code — including
`hw/xquartz/X11Controller.m` and `hw/xquartz/darwinEvents.c` in the
`src/xquartz/xserver` submodule — carries Apple's MIT-style notice:

> Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a
> copy of this software and associated documentation files (the
> "Software"), to deal in the Software without restriction, including
> without limitation the rights to use, copy, modify, merge, publish,
> distribute, sublicense, and/or sell copies of the Software, and to permit
> persons to whom the Software is furnished to do so, subject to the
> following conditions: [...] THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT
> WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED [...]

`quartz-wm` is licensed under the Apple Public Source License version 2
(APSL-2). Other components across the tree are licensed under MIT, BSD,
GPL-2, or LGPL-2, among others — check the specific submodule before
redistributing it in isolation.

## New contributions

Changes contributed to this repository are licensed under the same terms
as the file(s) they modify, as stated in that file's own header comment
where one exists. No separate restriction is added. There is no warranty
of any kind; use at your own risk, same as the rest of the project.

## Questions

For licensing questions about upstream XQuartz components, the project
directs people to the macOS X11 Users mailing list:
https://www.xquartz.org/Support.html
